FAQs

What are bonds?

Bonds are fixed-income securities that are issued either by government bodies or private institutions to raise funds through the debt market. The investors earn returns on their investment during a pre-decided tenure.

Learn more about bonds

How does the debt market work exactly?

Corporations need financing to acquire new customers, launch new products, or expand their business. To secure these funds, they can either go to equity markets and liquidate their holdings or look towards the debt market.

Issuing bonds in the debt market allows these institutions to raise funds without giving away their ownership.

Know more about the working of a debt market

What are Senior Secured bonds?

A secured bond is a bond that is backed by some kind of collateral like property or asset of the Issuer.

In case the Issuer is an NBFC, a secured bond is generally backed by a pool of personal, gold, and vehicle loans provided by the NBFC to its borrowers.

The term "senior" in a senior secured bond indicates that, in case of a default, these bondholders enjoy higher priority in getting repaid than some other types of investors like equity-holders, sub-debts etc.

Know more what happens when a NBFC defaults

Where do bonds fit in your portfolio?

Bonds open up a new asset class for your portfolio. An option with lower risk profile (compared to the equity market) and pre-decided returns.

In traditional investing options, the equity market offers high returns at the cost of increased risk and volatility while FDs offer stability with fixed returns but at the cost of low returns.

Bonds serve as the bridge here. With carefully curated bonds on Wint Wealth, you get 9-11% fixed returns in a short tenure of 1-3 years.

Full disclosure: Investing in bonds is riskier than FDs. Please do your due diligence before investing.

So, investing in bonds can add stability to your portfolio with fixed returns without you having to settle for lower returns.

I already invest in Mutual Funds, Equity and FDs. Why should I invest in bonds?

Bonds open up a new opportunity for your portfolio. Heres how:

In the long run, equity markets and Mutual Funds have the potential to give you high returns, but the returns are volatile and unpredictable in the short term.

On the other hand, traditional FDs give you fixed returns (predictable), but the returns are not high enough to beat inflation.

In this scenario, Bonds on Wint Wealth provide you with an option to earn higher returns (9-11%) than FDs with pre-decided returns and tenures that add predictability to your portfolios growth.

Learn more about bonds

Since the risks are higher compared to FDs, are there any added benefits to investing in bonds over them?

Yes, apart from earning higher returns for the higher risk, regular investment in bonds are an opportunity to:

Create a fixed income stream by earning 9-11% fixed returns on your money without settling for the low returns that FDs offer or depending on volatile equity markets.

Have one more basket for your eggs: Diversify your investments and add more stability to your portfolio.

In case the institution gets bankrupt, senior secured bondholders like you get a higher preference in repayment.

Does Wint Wealth do anything about the risks that are associated with investing in Bonds?

The bonds that go live on Wint Wealth are very carefully curated by our team of finance veterans. Here are some of the risk mitigation measures undertaken by them:

1) Debt-to-equity ratio: Called leverage in the world of finance, this ratio indicates the financial health of the NBFC. The maximum permissible limit for this by an NBFC is 5.66, post which RBI intervenes and can potentially revoke NBFCs license.

We list bonds from NBFCs with a leverage of less than 4 to ensure that the investment opportunities on our platform are comparatively safer than NBFCs with higher leverage.

2) High-Quality Institutional investors: The presence of institutional investors adds more credibility for the NBFC (Since these investors do their due diligence before investing) and indicates better levels of corporate governance.

Hence, all the bonds that we list are from NBFCs backed by experienced institutional investors.

3) Liability profile: The number and quality of lenders that the NBFC has also indicates their financial health. Hence, we take a close look at the diversity in their lenders before we decide to list their bonds.

Know more about how we partner with NBFCs

What documents do I need to invest in bonds?

To be able to invest in bonds on Wint Wealth, youll have to submit your KYC (takes 5 minutes). To complete your KYC submission, youll need your PAN card, Demat & bank account details, and Address proof details.
